<br>
Point 1, Thalaan<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Not all wizards have concussion, are you going to discriminate against them because of it? (I lost my VS faction before i was able to quest it)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Actually, yes.  You have to understand something here though...  I am not a level 40 cleric grouping in CoM or a level 50 cleric grouping in karnors...  I am a level 65 cleric grouping in elemental planes/tactics. (no I am not trying to brag here, so don't try and say I am, it's actually relevant)  If you are a 65 wizard and flagged for one of those zones and you never got concussion or ancient concussion, then you are lazy.  Don't try and pull bad faction out as an excuse.  My good friend Claud had the same problem and put off getting concussion until level 55 or so because he was too lazy to farm the venril sathir faction.  Not to mention you can use lull/invis while trade window open if your faction stinks.  Why would I discriminate against a wizard that either doesn't have or doesn't use concussion?  Because if you are casting concussion, you can cast more nukes while maintaining the same aggro level...  yes I know that inserting concussion uses mana and puts an interval of time between nukes as well which lowers the raw DPS of the spells you are casting, but it still will usually come out higher with concussion than without.  Higher DPS = faster kills and when each kill gives you 3.5% aaxp in a 6 person group, your kill rate can drastically affect how fast the xp comes in.  If all 6 people in the group are being inefficient, then your 1aaxp/hour becomes 1aaxp/2 hours.  Sorry, but my time is valuable and I would rather have a wizard that does more damage, and sustained high damage over time requires concussion.  It is not that unreasonable for me to ask this, since all the wizards I would group with in the first place are in raiding guilds and would have concussion for their uber boss fights... I would hope...<br>
<br>
Point 2, Izlaaru<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Euphrates I'll agree with most of what you say, as long as the comments are made AFTER the mistake is made and only as a side comment unless it happens more than once.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Thanks for the vote of confidence.  As stated above, I WON'T just come out and start telling wizards (or anyone in my group other than to designate who gets what jobs in case of multiple snarers or some similar situation, if they don't work it out amogst themselves first) how to play their class as soon as they join my group.  If they miss a snare once or over aggro or something, sure, I will be a little irritated but I won't really say anything until it happens again, at which time I might say something like, hey Wizardx, can you snare these please? just in case they were afk or thought we had another snarer or something.  If it continues to be a problem I will start becoming much less friendly and reasonable about it.  Things like that get groups killed and generally waste everyone's time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What spells I cast are up to me, as long as I'm doing my job<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, yes, I agree what spells you cast are up to you...  within reason.  I mean, as a cleric, if I was, say, using supernal light repeatedly to heal the tank (S-Light is a fast casting very large heal, ~1/2 a complete heal, that costs about 1.5 times the mana of complete heal) and getting aggro repeatedly because of it, as well as draining my mana twice as fast and then moaning to the group about how I was OOM, wouldn't you be a little upset with me?  It is the same situation here...  If you are casting your biggest nuke because it makes nice crits and that makes you feel warm and fuzzy, and you aren't concussioning at all, you keep getting summoned after these big nukes and I keep having to heal you because of it, or you snare too soon and get aggro on inc (there is NO REASON WHATSOEVER TO SNARE ON INCOMING) or have to back off and stop nuking because you keep overaggroing and refuse to use concussion, then I would say you are not doing your job effectively and if you refuse to listen to reasonable suggestions because YOU'RE THE WIZARD OMG AND YOU KNOW BEST, then have fun soloing or exercising your l33+ tactics in another group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As for concussion. If your looking at what spells are cast and counting them, I sure wouldn't want to be in your group.. I especially wouldn't want the tank cause it shows how much attention your paying to them!! I know I said Wizards w/out Concussion are crazy.. but I didn't say they were stupid.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't count spells and in fact I don't have time to read every single spell cast message etc that floats down my chat screen.  However, you have be blind to miss the occasional concussion in the spam of casting...  &quot;Target suffers from a blow to the head&quot; or whatever the message is is pretty distinctive and I can pick it out of text in my peripheral vision just by the length of the chat line and it's color...  Plus I won't even care until I start seeing the wizard have aggro problems, and it becomes obvious very shortly afterwards if you pay attention at all whether or not concussion is even being used.<br>
<br>
<br>
Point 3, Nadiar<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Strike of Solusek is one of our most efficient spells. In fact, its more efficient than draughts and rains. Euphrates, you have no idea how to play a wizard, and from what you say, you have no idea how to play a cleric either.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
SoS may be efficient or it may not, I have not bothered to look into this because I don't really care.  However, it IS your largest nuke (well, consistently) and therefore carries with it more aggro than others.  I am not saying that a wizard that uses SoS is a bad wizard...  but a wizard that can't control his aggro but still uses SoS is.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have played high end clerics, enchanters, paladins, wizards, and druids. I think I might know how to play my wizard better than you do. If I pull aggro, its because the tank isn't keeping up. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you pull aggro, it is most likely because of one of the following two reasons:<br>
<br>
1) As you state, the tank isn't keeping up/doing their job.  They're too busy jerking off with white rain to hit taunt and since you are used to them taunting you nuke accordingly and find yourself overaggroing.  In which case I heal you up and we all yell at the tank to taunt more.<br>
<br>
2) We yell at the tank to taunt more, and he says WTF, I have been taunting, disarming, begging on mezzed mobs, sitting when aggro goes to someone else, and I have my hate proc weapons equipped.  At this point (and only in this case) we have established that the tank is ACTUALLY DOING THEIR JOB, and it is you who is the fucktard overaggroing.  Yeah, so maybe this tank doesn't generate as much aggro as the one in your group yesterday.  If it is a problem, find a new tank, or a new group.  If you refuse to do either of those options, then it is your job to adjust your damage output and concussion ratio such that you don't overaggro anymore.<br>
<br>
You're such a good wizard and a smart person that you realized that though, and you were just testing me right?  I mean you wouldn't make blanket statements like 'If I pull aggro, its because the tank isn't keeping up' and actually mean it right, since obviously such a statement is situational?<br>
<br>
Point 4, Erumaron<br>
<br>
Thanks for the vote of confidence Erumaron.  I would like to point all you other wizards here reading this thread to erumaron's post.  He states that he tests his damage and adjusts according to the tank's ability to taunt etc.  This is a good way of doing things.  I have seen you wizards post on and on about how the best wizards ride the aggro line as tightly as they possibly can, maxing damage but managing aggro in such a way that if they get summoned they either don't get hit or they concussion once and the mob turns back to tank.  This is the type of wizard I expect in my group.<br>
<br>
<br>
Point 5, Kaisann<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you think SoS is an eye candy nuke perhaps you should step back and re-evaluate your knowledge of the class. Also, I really don't understand how you can have mana problems as a 65 cleric with even moderate gear. I happen to play one in xp groups all the time and I don't think I've ever gone below 80m with a slower + CC, 50m without one or the other. If you're in a group without both and the wizard pulls agro, feel free to let him die; I have no idea what your problem is otherwise. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sorry if my characterization of SoS as an eye candy nuke offends you.  It IS an eye candy nuke.  It is your biggest nuke... nuff said.  Note that just because it is *EYE CANDY* doesn't mean it is necessarily inefficient.  However, it would be narrow minded to ignore the fact that there are wizard who will use this nuke not for it's efficiency but because they get *BIG CRITS*.  Wizards tell me they are doing this sometimes, and I will humor them to some extent since it is a game.  The problem is that there are wizards who will just get excited by their crits and keep nuking, with little or no regard to aggro.<br>
<br>
As for my mana pool, yeah I have tons of mana regen but there are an insane number of mitigating factors here...  let me see...  PULL RATE would be a major factor, since mobs typically enter camp unslowed they deal a ton more damage than a slowed mob would, thus I have to heal more.  So if we are killing things quickly, more mobs come into camp in the same amount of elapsed time, meaning more unslowed damage to the tank in the same amount of time, meaning more mana expenditure, but more xp for the group...<br>
I may or may not have kei...  perhaps we are deep in plane of earth xping and it wears off.  I have the mana regen to continue to group, but I have to be more efficient about it.  Sometimes it isn't viable to gate out and refresh kei due to having to fight back to a spot that is now broken etc.  I try and maintain a mana reserve for adds, especially when we don't have a mezzer, if you are sucking up fast heals due to overaggro you are forcing me to dip into my reserves.  Also, if you are sucking up fast heals that means I am suddenly building way more aggro than I should have so now I may end up tanking an add or a mez break or even the single mob in camp.  Heal aggro sux, and clerics don't get the option of not casting the heal like wizards have the option of not casting the nuke.  Not to mention that if you are sucking up fast heals enough for it to be a problem, then it is likely that at some point no matter how hard I try, you will fuck up and die.  If you die I lose more mana rebuffing and healing you up, we lose damage while you med, and we lose xp while we recover.  So if you can just be a good wizard and manage your aggro, you will not set off a chain reaction of inefficiency.  Oh, I forgot probably the most important point: my fast heals are INEFFICIENT.  Supernal remedy costs EXACTLY THE SAME MANA AS COMPLETE HEAL.  So if you are forcing me to fast heal you when you have the ability to control it, you are forcing me to be inefficient.  This rather grates against my sensibilities, understandably so I think.<br>
<br>
Point 6, Faramir42<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Um, that is ripping on someone. In fact, that's so rude to tell another class how to play. Guess, what, if a cleric can't handle keeping everyone alive in a group, they suck as a cleric. If a tank can't keep aggro, or pull aggro off somene, they suck. I don't care if you are your God's right-hand man, I wouldn't never group with some one like you. <br>
<br>
