That being said, <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>SoS may be efficient or it may not, I have not bothered to look into this because I don't really care.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It is.  It doesn't matter if you look into it or not - it's more efficient than the alternatives you mentioned (are you trying to imply that we're making stuff up here?  Just go look it up - it'll take you 30 seconds). Besides that, any wizard that has it should know how to manage aggro with SoS vs. with Draughts.  If, by your own admission, you don't have the specific knowledge necessary to make a judgement on what spells the wizard should be using, then keep your specific opinions to yourself.  If the wizard is over-aggroing consistently, then tell him to watch his aggro, of course.  But spell selection is up to him.<br>
<br>
And just FYI, if you're in a pickup group, and the wizard hasn't grouped with the tank before, expect him to over-aggro reasonably often for the first few pulls.  That's him figuring out where the aggro line is for that tank, and that means he's doing his job correctly.  If the wizard is still pulling <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>hard</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> aggro <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>consistently</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> after 5 or 6 pulls, then he's doing something wrong, and you can (and should) call him on it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh, and just a tip - if a group member is causing a problem (over-aggro, snare issues, breaking mezzes), mention it to them, but I'd suggest using general terms (eg. &quot;watch your aggro please&quot;, &quot;careful with the AEs&quot;, etc.).  Once you start telling them which specific spells to use, you're basically saying that you know their class better than they do.  If you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>want</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to piss people off, that's a great way to do it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=euphrates>Euphrates</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 2:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Zarbonius:<br>
