Since you decided to disregard everything I said, perhaps I just need to establish my credentials.  I already stated that I play a 65 cleric all the time (read: daily for a few months) in XP groups.  I know the mana cost of your spells as well as you do.  I've grouped with wizards who pull agro with snare, shammies who ALWAYS slow on pull without debuffing, bards (enough said there!), stupid chanters, suicidal mages, shitty warriors, and monks who insist on pulling and I've never had anyone in my group die with the exception of two complete wipeouts thanks to massive overpulls.  I also have NEVER had to cast supernal remedy.  Never.  Not once.  In fact, I don't even keep it memmed, chosing instead to have celestial elixir up as a patch heal.  I've grouped without mana regen beyond BAotR and with Wind of Marr + VoQ, with and without CC/slow.<br>
<br>
Okay, enough of that.  I understand and sympathize with your concern over SR, but as I already said I can't understand why you'd worry about spending mana unless you were in a group without a slower AND CC.  In that case, I would definitely say something to an int caster drawing agro consistently.  Otherwise....only an incompetent shaman could possibly provoke a comment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yandidari>yandidari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/03 8:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Euphrates, wow you have flags to elementals and tactics, im like soooooo impressed. tactics flag means shit now, everyone 63 and over and get in, and just because you have elemental flags doesnt meant you're not an idiot. your guild got you the flag, you are still a moron and an ass. <br>
